# Established Brand Design System

- Optimize for an established, credible, industrial-tech brand expression.
- Prefer clean editorial layouts with strong hierarchy and disciplined whitespace.
- Use restrained color contrast and avoid overly saturated accents.
- Keep typography calm and legible; avoid novelty display styles.
- Maintain consistency in paddings, heading rhythm, and section spacing across pages.

## Visual Quality Checks

- Navigation and footer must feel consistent with the same design language.
- Hero and media sections should feel premium through crop, framing, and contrast control.
- Embedded media should sit in intentional containers with consistent spacing.
- Logo grids and partner marks must align cleanly with balanced visual weight.

## Motion

- Use minimal transitions (roughly 150ms to 250ms) for hover/focus/state changes.
- Avoid decorative animations unless they support comprehension.
